{"type":"message","id":"3e465738","parentId":"74d54af4","timestamp":"2026-04-15T01:52:41.517Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_3oc0upnry948_1","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"{\n  \"lastChecked\": \"2026-04-15T01:39:00Z\",\n  \"sessions\": {\n    \"cron:ed2d0b5d\": { \"status\": \"running\", \"label\": \"5p QLHV monitor\", \"note\": \"new instance running since ~01:13 UTC Apr 15 (prior instance completed normally ~01:13 UTC)\" },\n    \"cron:e7885813\": { \"status\": \"running\", \"label\": \"Agent Status to Lead\", \"note\": \"new instance running since ~01:16 UTC Apr 15 (prior instance completed normally ~01:16 UTC)\" },\n    \"cron:6f3323ef\": { \"status\": \"running\", \"label\": \"DTLX 5p Monitor\", \"note\": \"running ~11h 26m since ~23:13 UTC Apr 14\" },\n    \"cron:53c5832a\": { \"status\": \"done\", \"label\": \"Daily Briefing 5AM UTC+7\", \"note\": \"completed normally ~23:16 UTC Apr 14 — expected\" },\n    \"main\": { \"status\": \"done\", \"note\": \"ended normally at 00:46 UTC Apr 15 — expected\" },\n    \"telegram:direct:6053576134\": { \"status\": \"done\", \"label\": \"Lead direct\", \"note\": \"ended normally ~01:16 UTC Apr 15 — expected\" },\n    \"telegram:group:-5163901258\": { \"status\": \"done\", \"label\": \"Group monitoring\", \"note\": \"ended normally ~01:11 UTC Apr 15 — expected\" }\n  },\n  \"pipeline\": \"HEALTHY\",\n  \"blockers\": [],\n  \"deliveryIssues\": [\"telegram:group:-5163901258: sessions_send timeout — group session not replying to inter-session messages. Last confirmed delivery: 01:11 UTC Apr 15.\"],\n  \"noChangesSince\": null\n}\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1776217961515}}
{"type":"message","id":"9fef2ecb","parentId":"3e465738","timestamp":"2026-04-15T01:53:06.820Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now let me compare the current state (01:52 UTC) against the last heartbeat state (01:39 UTC).\n\n**Last known state (01:39 UTC):**\n- `cron:ed2d0b5d`: running ✅\n- `cron:e7885813`: running ✅\n- `cron:6f3323ef`: running ✅\n- `cron:53c5832a`: done ✅\n- `main`: done ✅\n- `telegram:direct:6053576134`: done ✅\n- `telegram:group:-5163901258`: done ✅\n\n**Current state (01:52 UTC) from sessions_list:**\n\n\nI'm seeing the same three cron jobs still running, with the DTLX 5p monitor having extended its duration to about 12 hours, while the others remain stable.\n\nLooking at the full session list, most of the work sessions are showing as completed or timed out, though there's a discrepancy where one telegram session is marked as running but also has an ended timestamp. The older cron jobs and subagent sessions are all in done or failed states, which explains why they're no longer appearing in the active list. I'm seeing a discrepancy in the session timestamps—the cron session shows endedAt at 01:47 UTC, but its last activity was at 01:50 UTC, suggesting the cron restarted after the previous check at 01:39 UTC. The group session also appears to have ended around 01:39 UTC, which might be affecting how these timings align. I've confirmed that both the QLHV monitor and DTLX cron are running at 01:52 UTC with their new instances, and the main session is still active. The pipeline is healthy with all three cron jobs operational, though there are no changes from the previous state since these are just normal 5-minute restarts. I'm realizing the heartbeat state from 01:39 UTC showed all sessions already marked as done, so at 01:52 UTC there are no actual changes to report on—everything has already been processed and wrapped up. I'm tracing through the session lifecycle more carefully now. The cron job `ed2d0b5d` that was marked as done at 01:39 UTC has actually restarted and is running again at 01:50 UTC—that's a state change I need to account for. Let me verify the timestamps: 1776217826897 converts to around 01:50 UTC, confirming the new instance is active, and the parent session shows it ran for about 10 seconds starting at 1776214290785. UTC), then it was done. Now it's running again.\n\nWait, let me check: the cron job was COMPLETED (done) at ~01:13 UTC and now is running again (new cycle started). This is normal 5-minute cron behavior - it completes a cycle and starts a new one. The question is whether this \"restart\" counts as a \"change\" worth reporting.\n\nLooking at the last heartbeat state at 01:39 UTC, it explicitly noted: \"new instance running since ~01:13 UTC\". So the state at 01:39 already reflected this as running. At 01:52 it's STILL running. No change in state from 01:39.\n\nWhat about the cron:6f3323ef DTLX 5p Monitor? At 01:39 it was running ~11h 26m (since ~23:13 UTC Apr 14). At 01:52 it's running ~12h 18m (since ~00:48 UTC Apr 15). That's just increased duration - the session is still running continuously.\n\nComparing the two snapshots: cron:ed2d0b5d and cron:e7885813 are still in the same running state, cron:6f3323ef has progressed from ~11h 26m to ~12h 18m which is normal session aging, and the other sessions remain done. No actual state changes occurred. So I should stay silent and not send anything. Looking at the current status of each cron job from the session data—the QLHV monitor has been running for about 13 minutes, the Agent Status job for roughly 21 minutes, and the DTLX 5p Monitor is at about 12 hours and 18 minutes—all of which are within expected operational ranges.\n\nSince none of these represent actual changes from the last reported state, the system remains stable and no notification is needed.","thinkingSignature":"18beb43a2dfa6327325c18a05856aa87321f1d91b271fbffc5d08083a6f10a0a"},{"type":"text","text":"**No changes detected.** Comparing current state (01:52 UTC) against heartbeat-state.json (01:39 UTC):\n\n- `cron:ed2d0b5d` — still running (new cycle, same state as 01:39) ✅\n- `cron:e7885813` — still running (new cycle, same state as 01:39) ✅\n- `cron:6f3323ef` — still running (normal session aging: 11h 26m → 12h 18m) ✅\n- All other sessions remain done/ended as previously noted ✅\n\nPipeline stable. Silent exit."}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","usage":{"input":541,"output":1050,"cacheRead":14264,"cacheWrite":31979,"totalTokens":47834,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1776217961522,"responseId":"062e226a23989dfd2194227f14212d6f"}}
